:: playchord
Give the chord a rest, and look at all the white keys on the keyboard. Have a play of some of them. We will use them in just a second.

 <img src="img/C_Major_straight.png" width="90%">

<<linkreplace "Tap to continue." t8n>>
Look at the chart again, specifically at the jagged line, which shows the total amount of ice, over time. 

 <img src="img/edited_SeaIce.png" width="90%">

We are going to play higher notes when the line is higher, and lower notes when the line is lower. Don’t play the whole chart just yet, we’ll do that soon. For the moment, think about this:

# Which key, on the keyboard, should you use for the first note?
# Which key should you use for the last note?
# What area of the keyboard should you be on, just after the year ‘2000’?

If you decide these things before starting, you won't accidentally start too high, or too low, and you won’t run out of keyboard at the end. You don’t need to remember these keys exactly, but having a rough idea is useful.

